Greetings to Tanzanian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Jakaya Mrisho Kikwete, President of Tanzania, on the occasion of the 44th anniversary of the United Republic of Tanzania on April 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger by common efforts, the message sincerely wished the Tanzanian people greater progress and prosperity.

Press Briefing on Pyongyang's Preparations for Olympic Torch Relay 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- A press briefing on the preparations of the Pyongyang function for the torch relay of the 29th Olympiad was held at the Yanggakdo International Hotel of the DPRK on April 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were reporters of the press in Pyongyang, foreign correspondents and officials of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Addressing the briefing, Ri Jong Sok, vice-chairman of the organizing committee of the Pyongyang function for the torch relay informed the participants of the itinerary of the Pyongyang function. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the function would be successfully held in safety on a high plane, saying that the opening ceremony would take place at the plaza of the Tower of the Juche Idea and the closing ceremony at Kim Il Sung Stadium.

National Seminar on Protection of Intellectual Property Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The National Seminar on the Protection of Intellectual Property was held at the People's Palace of Culture on April 23 and 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials in the fields of science, education, culture, arts, media, etc. and members of a delegation of the World Intellectual Property Organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Opening addresses were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Song Guk, vice-president of the State Administration for Quality Management, said that activities are brisk in the DPRK to raise the social awareness of intellectual property and create and protect intellectual goods conducive to social and economic life and cultural development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gao Hang, head of the delegation of the WIPO, in his speech dealt with the function and activities of the organization, importance of protection of intellectual property and institution of World IP Day, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the floor was taken by Choe Chi Ho, director of a department of the State Administration for Quality Management, Kim Hyon Il, senior instructor of a department of the SAQM, Anil Sinha, head of Executive and Research Program, the WIPO Worldwide Academy, Zhang Cheng, head of Trademark Supervision Division and Trademark Office of the State Administration for Industry and Commerce of China, and others under the titles " Protection of Intellectual Property in the DPRK and Its State Policy on It", "The Importance of Teaching and Training in Intellectual Property in Government Institutions, Universities and Research and Development Institutions", "Overview of Infringement of Patents and Trademarks", "Overview of the Protection and Administration of Intellectual Property in Other Countries", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers stressed the need to register greater successes in the protection of intellectual property, establish new theories on intellectual property to suit the history, culture and specific conditions of each country and nation, strengthen the work for protecting and encouraging intellectual property and develop exchange and cooperation among international organizations and other countries.

People's Delegations Visit KPA Units 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- People's delegations visited units of the Korean People's Army on the occasion of the 76th anniversary of the foundation of the heroic KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the members of the delegations arrived at the units, officers and men of the KPA warmly greeted them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members of the delegations conveyed news of the rear to the servicepersons, handed them the aid goods prepared by people with sincerity and went round units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They talked with servicepersons and had sports and amusement games with them. They renewed their resolutions to cement great army-people unity as firm as a rock and glorify Korean-style socialism.

Floral Baskets Laid before Statues of Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were laid before the statues of President Kim Il Sung by servicepersons of the People's Army and people from all walks of life on the occasion of the 76th anniversary of the founding of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons, people of different social standings and school youth and children in Pyongyang visited the statue of the President on Mansu Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before the statue was a floral basket sent by Supreme Commander of the KPA Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the statue were  floral baskets in the name of the party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, ministries, national institutions, KPA units and scientific, educational, cultural, art, public health and media institutions and factories,  enterprises and schools and bouquets and flowers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets were also laid before the statues of the President at Kim Il Sung Military University, Kim Il Sung Political University, Kim Il Sung University, the Ministry of People's Security, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other units in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons of the People's Army, people, school youth and children across the country visited the statues of the President in their residential areas to pay floral tribute to him.

Wreaths and Floral Baskets Laid 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery and floral baskets before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on the occasion of the 76th anniversary of the founding of the Korean People's Army on April 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries were wreaths sent by Supreme Commander of the KPA Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying and floral basket-laying ceremonies were Kim Yong Nam, Kim Yong Il, Kim Yong Chun, Kim Il Chol, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Ki Nam, Choe Yong Rim and Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party, and officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, social organizations, commissions of the Cabinet, ministries and national institutions, officers and men of the KPA and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths in the name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet were laid on the wreath-laying stands of the cemeteries and a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK was laid before the Statue "Victory", the main theme of the monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then wreaths and floral baskets in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, social organizations, commissions of the Cabinet, ministries, national institutions, KPA units and institutions of science, education, culture and arts, public health and press and the party and power organs, factories, farms and schools in Pyongyang were placed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, wreaths were also laid before the statues of martyrs, monuments to fallen fighters of KPA and cemeteries of martyrs in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the military attaches corps here laid a wreath before the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and a floral basket before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on the same occasion.

KPA Anniversary Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Leading papers Friday editorially celebrate the Army Day. They say that the foundation of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army by President Kim Il Sung on April 25, Juche 21 (1932) was a historic event which declared the birth of revolutionary army of new type guided by the Juche idea, the Songun idea in the era of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says: The nearly 80 year-long history of the KPA is a history in which it has won one victory after victory as a mainstay and a main force for the revolution, true to the idea and leadership of the party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spirit of devotedly defending the leader, the core in the mental power of the KPA, has been fully displayed on the noblest level in the Songun era led by Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victories on all fronts of the revolution and construction have been firmly guaranteed thanks to the great victory won on the anti-imperialist military front in the Korean revolution that was started and has advanced with arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Based on the victory and feats performed during the hard-fought great anti-Japanese war for Korea's liberation our party and the state were founded and the driving force for the revolution has grown remarkably stronger and the great victory won in the grim Fatherland Liberation War helped lay a reliable socio-political ground and military and economic foundation for the socialist revolution and socialist construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present stirring reality of Songun Korea which is dynamically advancing toward the bright morrow of a great prosperous powerful nation would be unthinkable without the devoted struggle of the Korean People's Army that has built lots of monumental edifices in the Songun era in different parts of the country overcoming manifold difficulties in the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il's Songun politics serves as an all-powerful treasured sword for the revolution and construction in our era and an ever-victorious banner for frustrating the imperialists' hegemonic strategy because it helped defend socialism and usher in the dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation despite the worst adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under the banner of Songun provided by the great brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu, the KPA has demonstrated its might as an invincible revolutionary army matchless in ideology, mentality and combat capacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA is an invincible revolutionary army strong in ideology and faith, being possessed of indefatigable mental power, invincible Juche-based war methods and powerful striking capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA is invincible revolutionary armed forces strongly supported and helped by all people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that it is the immense honor and pride of the Korean people to have the KPA which has demonstrated its might as a powerful revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu under the guidance of the President and Kim Jong Il.

South Korea-U.S. Military Confab against DPRK Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The 14th south Korea-U.S. seminar on defense analysis recently held under the co-sponsorship of the Institute for Defense Studies of south Korea and the institute of analysis and concept of the U.S. army was an extremely dangerous military confab as it reconfirmed the master-servant military relationship between the U.S. and south Korea and the U.S. forces' permanent presence in south Korea and discussed the moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK with the south Korean pro-U.S. conservative ruling groups. Minju Joson Friday observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar brought to light the intention of the U.S. military chiefs to make the south Korean forces more faithfully serve it as puppet forces and use them as a shock brigade in carrying out the war against the DPRK. It also disclosed the idea of the south Korean pro-U.S. conservative ruling groups subservient to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korea-U.S. "alliance" is an "alliance" for aggression and a war "alliance" against the DPRK in every aspect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the alliance the U.S. seeks to make south Korea increasingly dependent upon it politically and militarily and use the south Korean puppet forces as servants in executing its war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lee Myung Bak group is running wild, talking about "priority to south Korea-U.S. alliance" and tightened relationship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality proves that the U.S. is talking about "dialogue" and "peace" before its dialogue partner but working hard to do harm to it in collusion with the south Korean warhawks behind the scene. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean pro-U.S. conservative ruling group should clearly understand that they will get nothing but a shameful destruction if they keep acting puppets and henchmen of the U.S. with their backs turned on fellow countrymen.

Independent Reunification Called for in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in south Korea made public a statement on April 19 on the occasion of the 48th anniversary of the April popular uprising. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the April 19 uprising was mass resistance staged by the people from all walks of life against the Syngman Rhee dictatorial forces' moves against democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Lee Myung Bak regime is persistently pursuing confrontation with compatriots, following the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK, it called upon the youth and students to inherit the April 19 spirit and take the lead in the struggle to achieve independent reunification, peace and prosperity by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation.

Abolition of NSL Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, demanded the abolition of the notorious "National Security Law" (NSL) at a court on April 11. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that during the past days when he was wanted by the police it broke into his house frequently and resorted to open appeasement and threat in a bid to prod his parents into cooperating with its investigation while accusing them "of having a son charged with espionage", he declared that he would fight against the NSL to the last as it made him a "criminal" by branding the reunification movement as a "crime".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Remarkable successes which could hardly be seen in the past have been achieved in the reunification movement thanks to the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, he noted, adding that the NSL is desperately blocking the way of the development of the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the abolition of the evil law is, indeed, a primary task facing the reunification movement, he demanded the court authorities face up to the present times and make a proper judgment.

Lee Myung Bak's Junket to U.S. under Fire in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification in south Korea issued a statement on April 21 denouncing Lee Myung Bak for his servile and submissive act. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It accused him of advertising the agreement reached on a stop to the reduction of the U.S. forces in south Korea and the conclusion of the FTA within the year as a "success" made during his visit to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It recalled that during his trip to the U.S. he begged for a stop to the reduction of the U.S. forces in south Korea and, in return for this, agreed to actively cooperate with the U.S. in its "anti-terrorist war" and "improve the system of sharing the upkeep of the U.S. forces", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The " strategic alliance in the 21st century" touted by Lee is an anti-peace outburst calling for helping the U.S. realize its ambition for world supremacy, it said, stating that the moves for "future initiative for south Korea-U.S. alliance" in which it is put into a concrete shape should be stopped at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will join the people desirous of independence, peace and reunification and wage a bold struggle to shatter the plot to tighten the aggressive and humiliating "alliance" with U.S. and force the U.S. forces to withdraw from south Korea, declared the statement.

Kim Il Sung's Work Off Press in Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung's work "On the Three Principles of National Reunification" was brought out in booklet by the Enugu Publishing House of Nigeria on April 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preface of the booklet says that Kim Il Sung clearly indicated the orientation and ways of achieving the cause of national reunification in many works including "On the Three Principles of National Reunification".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification and a bright prospect of reunification have been recently opened in the DPRK under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, it notes, adding that this proves the validity of the reunification policy advanced by Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The publishing house is convinced that this work will help readers know better about the feats Kim Il Sung performed by devoting his all to the reunification of Korea, it concludes.

Day of Sun Observed in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Sweden and Bulgaria and a seminar took place in Finland on April 12 and 15 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Christer Lundgren, chairman of the Sweden-Korea Friendship Association, speaking at a meeting, said that the Day of the Sun is a common holiday of not only the Korean people but the world progressive people. The Korean people are holding Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the father of socialist Korea, the father of the nation and the eternal President of the DPRK, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vasilka Nikiforova, chief of the "Kim Il Sung Library" in Sofia of Bulgaria, and Maria Nikiforova, secretary general of the Bulgaria-Korea Friendship Association, in their speeches at a meeting said that the feats performed by Kim Il Sung, the founder of the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK, will last forever. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the future of Korea is bright and the cause of world socialism is sure to triumph thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il who is building the DPRK into a socialist power which no one dares provoke, true to the behest of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Juha Kieksy, chairman of the Finnish National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, Esko Koskinen, chairman of the Finland-Korea Society, and Sika Aho Antti, chief of the Finnish Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Jong Il, in their speeches stressed that the Juche idea founded by Kim Il Sung serves as a beacon of hope as it clearly indicates the way to be followed by the progressive people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings.

Japan's Liquidation of Its Past Wrongdoings Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- A meeting of coordinators of the International Solidarity Consultative Council for Demanding Japan's Liquidation of Its Past Wrongdoings was held in Manila on April 19 and 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were representatives and figures of organizations of various countries and regions affiliated to the council including the DPRK, China, Philippines, Indonesia and Netherlands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting heard speeches about the activities conducted by the above-said organizations last year in demand of Japan's liquidation of its past wrongdoings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Discussed there were a program for future activities including the expansion of the actions demanding Japan settle its past crimes against humanity and stop distorting its history to the U.S. and Europe, the issue of widely organizing diverse activities demanding  Japan liquidate its past wrongdoings in various countries with August 15 this year as a momentum, the issue of jointly publishing the book introducing the damage done by Japan's inhuman crimes to various countries and regions and international solidarity activities for its settlement and the issue of building up world public opinion on the issue of remains of the Korean draftees and the ways to implement it.

Japan's Extension of Sanctions against DPRK Assailed by Koreans in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans in Japan conducted information services in different parts of Japan to denounce the Japanese authorities' extension of the sanctions against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials under the Hyogo Prefectural Headquarters of Chongryon conducted information services in Amagasaki City on April 11, timed to coincide with the Japanese authorities' third extension of the sanctions against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to it, on April 8, officials of the headquarters staged a protest around Sannomiya Railway Station and Hime area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials under the Aomori Prefectural Headquarters of Chongryon and compatriots conducted information services in Aomori City on April 7 demanding the Japanese authorities immediately lift the embargo on "Mangyongbong-92".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Koreans in Japan are undergoing hardships, unable to meet with their kin in the homeland owing to the unreasonable sanctions, they urged the Japanese authorities to lift the sanctions at once.

Seminar of Koreans in Osaka on National Education Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- A seminar of Koreans in Osaka on national education was held in Osaka on April 18 to mark the 60th anniversary of the April 24 struggle for education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) including those related to national education, compatriots and students in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A reporter and speakers said that they were marking the 60th anniversary of the April 24 struggle for education at a time when the struggle of compatriots to defend and develop national education as well as the movement to invite compatriots to come to the fold of Chongryon set forth at its 21st Congress are now under way across Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that the compatriots defended their schools by their concerted efforts despite the harsh suppression by the U.S. and Japanese authorities to obliterate national education of Koreans in Japan in 1948. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They denounced the Japanese authorities for persistently pursuing the policy of discriminating against Korean schools, refusing to admit the right of Koreans in Japan to national education though 60 years have passed since then. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the history and prospect of national classes, the issue to be settled in defending and expanding the right to national education and the importance of the work to bring up children in the Korean community, they stressed the need to defend and develop the national education, which had been gained by compatriots of the first and second generations at the cost of blood and sweat, by the efforts of the third and fourth generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal was read out at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Letters of solidarity were sent to the seminar by Eiichi Yamashita, secretary general of the Dietmen's League for Supporting Foreign Schools and Education of Children of Foreigners in Japan, members of the Osaka Prefectural Assembly and Japanese figures supporting Korean schools.

Meeting Held to Extend Thanks to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- A meeting of officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and compatriots was held at the Korean Primary School in Nagoya, Aichi Prefecture, on April 23 to extend thanks to General Secretary Kim Jong Il for sending educational aid fund and stipends for the democratic and national education of children of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, Ryang Ok Chul, director of the Educational Department of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee, other leading officials of organizations and enterprises and Chongryon officials, educational workers, scientists, Korean students studying at Japanese schools and compatriots in Tokai area . &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ku Tae Sok, chairman of the Central Standing Council of the Korean Education Association in Japan, in a report said that Kim Jong Il sent educational aid fund and stipends amounting to 205 million yen again on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. He extended highest glory and warmest thanks to Kim Jong Il, who has invariably carried forward the history of the noble love of President Kim Il Sung, representing the warm feelings of all compatriots in Japan.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The graduates from Korean schools who grew up, benefited from the educational aid fund and stipends, are making a positive contribution to developing the Korean community and building a great prosperous powerful nation and active in the international arena as pillars for the patriotic work and intellectuals of the nation, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon all Koreans in Japan to bear deep in mind the history of national education recorded with the love of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, inherit the patriotic feats performed by the preceding generations and the tradition established by them and thus put the national education on a new higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed speeches by representatives of Koreans of different social standings in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of thanks to Kim Jong Il was read out at the meeting.

Informacion sobre preparativos para carrera de antorcha olimpica
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de abril (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar la vispera en el Hotel Internacional Yanggakdo el acto de informacion sobre los preparativos para la carrera de relevos de la antorcha de los XXIX Juegos Olimpicos en Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la ocasion estuvieron presentes los reporteros de la rama de prensa e informacion en esta capital, los corresponsales extranjeros y los miembros de la embajada china en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El vicepresidente del comite organizador de la carrera de relevos en Pyongyang, Ri Jong Sok, informo sobre el programa de esta actividad olimpica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El preciso que el acto inaugural se efectuara en la explanada frente al Monumento a la Idea Juche y el de clausura, en el Estadio Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Aseguro que la carrera de relevos en esta capital se realizara magnifica, segura y exitosamente en un alto nivel.

Delegaciones del pueblo felicitan el dia de la fundacion del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de abril (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 76o aniversario de la fundacion del heroico Ejercito Popular de Corea, las delegaciones del pueblo visitaron las unidades del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los oficiales y soldados del EPC acogieron cordialmente a los miembros de las delegaciones, quienes transmitieron a los militares las noticias de la retaguardia, les entregaron los articulos de ayuda impregnados de la sinceridad del pueblo y recorrieron las unidades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien, los visitantes departieron con los militares, hicieron juegos deportivos y recreativos con estos y expresaron determinaciones de consolidar con firmeza la gran unidad entre el ejercito y el pueblo y glorificar el socialismo coreano.
